LINE.Text: Christmas is a time for giving, for sharing, for considering those less fortunate
than ourselves and for family. Or so we're told. Here's what the population of
the United Kingdom really does at Christmas.
250 million pints & 35 million bottles of wine
ON AVERAGE, EACH PERSON IN THE UK BUYS PRESENTS FOR 8.7 OTHER PEOPLE
1 IN 40 ADULTS RECEIVED A KINDLE OR OTHER E -READER FOR XMAS LAST YEAR
65% of people don' leave out a stocking
4% of people don't know whether they leave out a stocking or not!
1% OF PEOPLE DON'T OPEN THEIR PRESENTS UNTIL AFTER Christmas DAY!
1.7 BILLION Christmas CARDS WERE WRITTEN IN THE UK LAST YEAR
JUST 33 % OF PEOPLE SAY THEY WILL ATTEND CHURCH SOMETIME OVER CHRISTMAS
OVER 20% OF BRITISH MEN SAY THEY HAVE KISSED A COLLEAGUE AT A WORK PARTY
Sources: YouGov.co.uk, JP Events and Exhibitions
